01:50:50.945 --> 01:50:52.413
(SNIFFLES)

01:50:55.149 --> 01:50:57.951
SIDNEY: Once Melody left me,

01:50:59.053 --> 01:51:00.553
it dawned on me,

01:51:00.554 --> 01:51:04.724
looking out at all those
wonderful city lights,

01:51:04.725 --> 01:51:09.762
that I was just one of those
millions of city lights,

01:51:09.763 --> 01:51:12.366
a tiny little pixel,

01:51:12.900 --> 01:51:16.569
buried within
the white noise of life,

01:51:16.570 --> 01:51:22.075
blinking on for just
a brief second in time.

01:51:27.114 --> 01:51:29.549
I didn't want to be a martyr.

01:51:29.550 --> 01:51:31.685
I wanted to be nobody.

01:51:35.189 --> 01:51:38.057
And I walked out
of that apartment

01:51:38.058 --> 01:51:41.094
with only the clothes
on my back.

01:51:42.396 --> 01:51:44.732
To become nobody.

01:51:45.733 --> 01:51:48.101
I never returned again.

01:51:57.978 --> 01:52:00.681
(INAUDIBLE)

01:52:25.773 --> 01:52:30.277
I just keep replaying
that scene.

01:52:31.245 --> 01:52:37.284
Hoping against hope
that the ending would change.

01:52:37.585 --> 01:52:43.890
That she would just wake up…

01:52:43.891 --> 01:52:47.127
And say, "Sidney…

01:52:47.227 --> 01:52:48.862
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:52:52.901 --> 01:52:55.903
"I'm not leaving you just yet.

01:52:59.874 --> 01:53:02.509
"I'm still pregnant."

01:53:13.221 --> 01:53:15.288
Sidney.

01:53:30.337 --> 01:53:33.907
(TOMORROW IS A LONG TIME
PLAYING)

